comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-24T08:42:52.228Z",codex-gpt5,"Continuation: PR #353 is still open with failing Gates (coverage) and Gates (smokes) on head 5bd07b82. Reopening/continuing the existing TypeScript-only extension loading lineage instead of creating a duplicate item. Root failure: beads/todos package commands cannot resolve runtime.ts from the package-first installed path; review follow-up also requires tsconfig.examples allowImportingTsExtensions, scaffold engines.node >=22.18.0, Node 22 TS-loading smoke coverage, and pm-frou metadata reconciliation via pm."
  "2026-06-24T09:14:36.493Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence: PR #353 follow-up fixes are implemented and locally verified. Fixed package runtime-loader missing-module classification so missing dependencies inside discovered runtime.ts are rethrown instead of being swallowed as a missing runtime. Added Node 22 dist smoke for TS package runtime loading, tsconfig.examples allowImportingTsExtensions, scaffold package engines.node >=22.18.0, and pm-frou metadata reconciliation. Focused checks passed: gen-package-runtime-loaders --check; runtime-loader/scaffold/CI contract tests 30 passed; CI failure slice 3 passed; pnpm dogfood:package-first 88 commands ok. Full gates passed: pnpm typecheck; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage = 248 files, 4993 tests, 100/100/100/100; quality:static; quality:docs-skills; contracts:check; changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog latest npm version 2026.6.20; security:scan; pnpm audit --audit-level low; version:check; compatibility-check; npm pack --dry-run; pm health --check-only; pnpm smoke:external-packages tested 10 packages with 0 failures; pnpm release:gates passed end to end. Manual temp-dir smoke passed at /tmp/tmp.YPXDQmEAE4 using isolated PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH: init, create, install beads/todos one-at-a-time, beads import, todos export, scaffold/install starter-extension, run starter extension ping, extension doctor strict summary with 3 active runtimes and 0 warnings, health ok. GitHub reports checked: PR #353 had stale failures on previous head; open issue #348 is related to unsupported Node 20 nightly and is linked to pm-2kkl; branch nightly matrix no longer includes Node 20. Dependabot/code-scanning/secret-scanning alert APIs returned 404/not enabled or not visible to token, while local secret scan and pnpm audit are green. Sentry/telemetry gate checked unbrained/pm-cli over 14 days: 0 critical, 0 high, 11 expected CLI-error issues ignored, telemetry finish error rate 0.86%, missing error-code rows 0."
  "2026-06-24T09:19:21.161Z",codex-gpt5,"CI follow-up: PR #353 head 370e7fc8 failed Runtime smoke (ubuntu-latest, Node 22) job 83159442244. Root cause: the dependency-free runtime-smoke job only supports the dist fast --version path; running full CLI commands requires node_modules (missing commander). Fix direction: keep the smoke dependency-free and exercise Node 22 TypeScript loading by importing packages/pm-beads/extensions/beads/runtime-loader.ts directly against a temp runtime.ts via PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT."
  "2026-06-24T09:42:49.095Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence update after PR #353 head 370e7fc8 CI failures: fixed Runtime smoke (ubuntu-latest, Node 22) by replacing full CLI commands in the dependency-free job with a direct runtime-loader.ts import against a temp runtime.ts under PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT; reproduced locally with mise node@22.21.1 and the workflow command passed. Fixed Gates (smokes) package-first failure by making pm-beads and pm-todos runtimes keep public SDK type imports but load runtime values from PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT/dist/sdk/index.js during real CLI/package execution, with source-sdk fallback only for no-env source tests so hook/mocking state stays shared. Focused verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/packages/beads-command.spec.ts tests/unit/packages/todos-extension.spec.ts tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts = 4 files / 72 tests passed; node scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs --check passed; pnpm dogfood:package-first passed with 88 commands; Node 22 smoke command passed; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan found no tracked-file secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level low found no known vulnerabilities; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed at exact 100/100/100/100 with 248 files and 4997 tests. pnpm changelog:pm:check is currently expected to fail while this item is reopened/in_progress because CHANGELOG.md was generated from closed items; next step is closing pm-2p7a again and regenerating/checking the pm-changelog output."
  "2026-06-24T09:50:26.029Z",codex-gpt5,"Final local verification before push: pnpm quality:docs-skills passed; node scripts/release/compatibility-check.mjs --json passed with validation_ok=true and health_ok=true; PM_AUTHOR=codex-gpt5 pm health --check-only --summary --json passed with warning_count=0; node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --json --telemetry-mode best-effort --sentry-window-days 14 --max-critical 0 --max-high 0 passed with Sentry critical=0/high=0, 11 expected CLI-error issues ignored, telemetry finish error rate 0.85%, and missing error-code rows=0; pnpm smoke:external-packages passed with 10 tested and 0 failures; pnpm release:gates passed, including exact 100/100/100/100 coverage, npx packed package smoke, and package-first dogfood 88 commands."
  "2026-06-24T09:58:02.730Z",codex-gpt5,"Review disposition: Gemini Code Assist current-head feedback suggested lowering the Node floor to >=22.12.0 because v22.18.0 allegedly does not exist. Verified against the official Node.js v22.18.0 release notes and Node TypeScript native-run docs: v22.18.0 exists and is the no-flag type-stripping floor, so no code change is appropriate."
  "2026-06-24T10:13:12.100Z",codex-gpt5,"Review fix evidence: addressed unresolved Gemini Windows path-normalization thread by updating scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs so generated runtime loaders compare ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND messages against both native modulePath and forward-slashed normalizedModulePath before falling back. Regenerated pm-beads and pm-todos runtime-loader.ts and added regression coverage in tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts using a backslash-containing temp root with a forward-slashed error message. Verification passed: node scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.spec.ts = 26 tests; pnpm typecheck; pnpm quality:static; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage = 248 files, 4999 tests, exact 100/100/100/100; pnpm contracts:check; pnpm security:scan; pnpm dogfood:package-first = 88 commands. Manual temp smoke passed at /tmp/tmp.m7DE9LYlja with isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH: init, install beads/todos, beads import imported=1, todos export exported=2, package doctor strict ok with 0 warnings, health ok with telemetry_queue_pending warning from the manual actions."
  "2026-06-24T10:37:40.396Z",codex-gpt5,"Current-head review fix evidence: addressed Gemini and CodeRabbit feedback by preserving dynamic SDK import failures as Error.cause in pm-beads and pm-todos runtimes, and by tightening SDK guard validation so beads requires numeric EXIT_CODE.NOT_FOUND and EXIT_CODE.USAGE while todos requires numeric EXIT_CODE.NOT_FOUND before accepting the configured SDK module. Added tests for missing SDK root cause preservation and incomplete EXIT_CODE rejection. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/packages/beads-command.spec.ts tests/unit/packages/todos-extension.spec.ts = 47 tests; pnpm typecheck; pnpm quality:static; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage = 248 files, 5001 tests, exact 100/100/100/100; pnpm contracts:check; pnpm security:scan; pnpm dogfood:package-first = 88 commands; manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.g9FwUfBFQm with isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH passed with beads import=1, todos export=2, package doctor strict warnings=0, health warnings=0; pnpm audit --audit-level low; Sentry/telemetry gate critical/high=0/0, telemetry error rate=0.85%, missing error-code rows=0; pnpm smoke:external-packages tested 10 packages with 0 failures; pnpm quality:docs-skills."
